## wheeler-tools CLI (Deterministic Operations)

Build a Typer CLI for mechanical operations that would waste tokens if 
Claude generated them ad-hoc:

```
wheeler-tools graph init              # Apply schema constraints + indexes
wheeler-tools graph status            # Node/edge counts
wheeler-tools graph add-finding       # Create Finding node
wheeler-tools graph add-question      # Create OpenQuestion node
wheeler-tools graph link              # Create relationship between nodes

wheeler-tools validate <response>     # Citation validation (the critical one)
wheeler-tools validate --file resp.md # Validate from file

wheeler-tools plan create             # Create Plan node
wheeler-tools plan advance            # Mark task complete

wheeler-tools state show              # Current session state
wheeler-tools state set-mode          # Change mode

wheeler-tools graph stale             # Compare script hashes on disk to stored values,
                                      # flag findings with changed upstream analyses

wheeler-tools ledger show             # Recent ledger entries
wheeler-tools ledger query            # Query provenance trail
```

