## Implementation Order

### Phase 1: Graph + Validation Foundation
1. Docker Neo4j setup
2. Install `neo4j-agent-memory` and extend MemoryClient with Wheeler schema
3. Schema initialization (constraints, indexes, Analysis nodes with full provenance properties)
4. Citation extraction (regex, pure Python, no Neo4j needed to test)
5. Citation validation (Cypher queries against Neo4j)
6. Provenance ledger data model
7. wheeler-tools graph commands
8. wheeler-tools validate command

### Phase 2: Engine + Modes  
1. WheelerEngine wrapping Agent SDK with mode-aware ClaudeAgentOptions
2. Mode state machine with allowed_tools per mode
3. System prompts with citation rule
4. Graph context injection (size-limited)
5. Interactive CLI loop with slash commands
6. Post-response validation hook (run after every Claude response)

### Phase 3: MCP Servers
1. mcp-neo4j-cypher configuration
2. matlab-mcp-tools setup (requires MATLAB Engine API, Python 3.10/3.11)
3. paper-search-mcp setup
4. Subagent definitions for execute mode

### Phase 4: Writing + Polish
1. Writing mode with enforced citation checking
2. Session save/resume
3. Provenance queries ("how did we get to this finding?")
4. wheeler-tools ledger commands

