## Key Technical Notes

- Python 3.11 required (MATLAB Engine API constraint)
- Agent SDK: `pip install claude-agent-sdk` (bundles Claude Code CLI)
- Graph memory: `pip install neo4j-agent-memory` (extend MemoryClient with Wheeler schema)
- Agent SDK confirmed working on Max subscription (no API charges)
- Neo4j Community Edition: free, GPLv3, Docker one-liner
- Mode enforcement via allowed_tools (not hooks) — cleaner, Claude never sees blocked tools
- Subagents in execute mode get fresh 200k context each (GSD pattern)
- Keep orchestrator context < 15%, each agent < 50%
- Size-limit all injected context (5 findings, 5 questions, 3 hypotheses)
- Deterministic validation ONLY — never use Claude to validate Claude's own citations